    <main>
        <div class="mission-box">
            <strong>The Mission:</strong> We believe that "Peace and Quiet" is often just a synonym for social stagnation. Our algorithm doesn't track silence; it tracks <strong>participation</strong>. We help you find the places where the heartbeat of the city is loudest.
        </div>

        <h1>The Science of the Vibe</h1>
        <p>At <span class="highlight">VibrantAndVocal</span>, we use 100% organic, publicly available data to measure the life force of a neighborhood. While other maps help you hide, we help you arrive.</p>

        <h2>The Vibe Index (VI) Formula</h2>
        <div class="formula">
            VI = (Spice * Polyglot) / (Gatekeeping + HOA)
        </div>
        <p style="font-size: 14px; color: #666;">
            * <strong>Spice:</strong> Density of independent, non-chain restaurants per sq mile.<br>
            * <strong>Polyglot:</strong> Number of unique languages identified in local business registries.<br>
            * <strong>Gatekeeping:</strong> Number of "No Trespassing" signs and private security cameras.
        </p>

        <h2>Our Primary Data Layers</h2>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Acoustic Vitality:</strong> We prioritize areas where the sound of human existence—music, street markets, and conversation—thrives. High decibels equal high soul.</li>
            <li><strong>Inclusive Name Analytics:</strong> We use census and voter data to reward areas with high cultural variance. A neighborhood where everyone has the same origin is flagged as a "Low-Energy Zone."</li>
            <li><strong>The Scent Trail:</strong> We track business licenses for international grocers. If your neighborhood doesn't smell like cilantro, garlic, or curry by 6:00 PM, your Vibe Index drops significantly.</li>
        </ul>

        <p style="margin-top: 40px; font-style: italic; border-top: 1px solid #eee; padding-top: 20px;">
            Note: We do not track "peace." We track "pulse." If a neighborhood is too quiet, our system automatically classifies it as a <strong>Cultural Desert</strong>.
        </p>
    </main>

